s from poorer regions of the world—discussed innovative proposals that anticipated more contemporary debates about how to reconcile the existing liberal global economic order with the development aspirations of emerging powers such as India, China, and Brazil. Alongside the much-studied Anglo-American relationship was an overlooked but pioneering North-South dialogue. Helleiner’s unconventional history brings to light not only these forgotten foundations of the Bretton Woods system but also their subsequent neglect after World War II.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aEconomic developmentxHistoryy20th century. 0aInternational financexHistoryy20th century. 4aHistory. 4aPolitical Science & Political History.  aDevelopment Studies.  aGlobal Political Economy.  aGood Neighbor financial partnership.  aUS financial diplomacy.  aamerican history .  abooks on economic development.  abooks on international development.  acreation of the international monetary fund.  adiplomacy.  adogmengeschichte of development.  aeconomic development of latin america.  aeconomic development.  aeconomic history.  aeconomic progress.  afinancial advisory mission to Cuba.  aglobal economy.  aglobal finance.  ahistory .  ahistory of economic development.  ahistory of international business.  ahistory of international finance.  ahistory of international monetary affairs.  ahistory of the international monetary system.  ainternational economic progress.  ainternational finance.  alatin american development.  amodern economic history.  anorth-south relations.  aorigins of international development.  apolitical economy.  apolitical science.  apolitical studies.  apost-war financial institutions.  apostwar global economic order.  apostwar international economic order.  apost